---
@@aREINCARNATION@@W

Reincarnation is the endgame progression system for Realm Lords — characters
who have reached adept level 20 in any adept class. When you reincarnate, you
are reborn as a level 1 character of your chosen race and class order, but
carry forward permanent bonuses earned from your previous lives.

@@ySyntax:@@W
  reincarnate information
  reincarnate buy help
  reincarnate buy damcap
  reincarnate buy statcap
  reincarnate set show
  reincarnate set race <race>
  reincarnate set order <class1> <class2> <class3> <class4>
  reincarnate set confirm
  reincarnate set done

@@yRequirements:@@W
  You must have an adept class level of 20 (Realm Lord) to use
  reincarnate set. Use @@Wreincarnate information@@W at any level to view
  your accumulated bonuses.

@@yThe Reincarnation Process:@@W
  1. Choose your new race: @@Wreincarnate set race <race>@@W
     Any player-allowed race is valid. See @@Wrlist@@W for options.

  2. Choose your new class order: @@Wreincarnate set order <c1> <c2> <c3> <c4>@@W
     Specify all four mortal class slots. Example:
       reincarnate set order War Cle Thi Psi

  3. Confirm your selections: @@Wreincarnate set confirm@@W
     Review first with @@Wreincarnate set show@@W.

  4. Execute: @@Wreincarnate set done@@W
     This is irreversible. Your character is reborn at level 1.

@@yWhat Happens When You Reincarnate:@@W
  - All equipped items are removed.
  - Your experience is converted to quest points: (exp / 100000) + 1.
  - Your level, class levels, remort levels, and adept levels all reset to 0.
  - Your HP/Mana/Move gains from leveling are banked as permanent bonuses.
  - You receive 1 reincarnation point to spend on upgrades.
  - Your reincarnation history is updated (mortal, remort, and adept counts).
  - You begin again at level 1 with your chosen race and class order.

@@yPersistent Bonuses — HP, Mana, and Move:@@W
  The HP, mana, and move you gained from leveling are permanently banked.
  These bonuses apply every level in future lives, scaled with diminishing
  returns. Each reincarnation adds to this pool, so the bonus grows over
  multiple lives. Buying a higher statcap (see below) raises the threshold
  before diminishing returns kick in.

@@yPersistent Bonuses — Stat Caps:@@W
  Each mortal class reincarnation raises the stat cap for that class's
  prime attribute by 1 point for every 2 reincarnations in that class
  (rounds up). The stat cap is normally @@W30@@W.
  - @@cWarrior@@W reincarnations increase max Strength.
  - @@pMage@@W and @@GPsionicist@@W reincarnations increase max Intelligence.
  - @@aClerical@@W reincarnations increase max Wisdom.
  - @@dThief@@W reincarnations increase max Dexterity.
  - @@gPugilist@@W reincarnations increase max Constitution.

@@yPersistent Bonuses — Skill Unlocks (Mortal):@@W
  Having at least 1 reincarnation in a mortal class permanently unlocks
  a skill regardless of your current class:
  - @@cWarrior@@W    -> Enhanced Damage
  - @@dThief@@W      -> Enhanced Critical
  - @@gPugilist@@W   -> Counter
  - @@pMage@@W       -> Potency
  - @@GPsionicist@@W -> Spell Critical
  - @@aCleric@@W     -> Spell Critical Damage

@@yPersistent Bonuses — Skill Unlocks (Remort):@@W
  Combined remort reincarnation totals of 20 or more unlock skills:
  - Assassin + Warlock >= 20     -> Dual Wield
  - Knight + Swordsman >= 20     -> Two-Handed, Equip Buckler
  - Paladin + Priest >= 20       -> Two-Handed, Equip Buckler, Equip Wand
  - Brawler + Monk >= 20         -> Equip Fist, Dual Fist
  - Wizard + Sorcerer >= 20      -> Equip Wand
  - Necromancer + Egomancer >= 20 -> Equip Wand

@@yPersistent Bonuses — Damage Cap:@@W
  The base damage cap is @@W2500@@W (adepts gain +500 while adept). Each
  purchased damcap upgrade adds a permanent @@W+500@@W to your damage cap.

@@yReincarnation Points — Spending:@@W
  Each reincarnation grants 1 reincarnation point. Use @@Wreincarnate buy@@W
  to spend them on permanent upgrades. Use @@Wreincarnate buy help@@W to see
  the cost for your next upgrade.

  @@wreincarnate buy damcap@@W
    Permanently increases your damage cap by 500.
    Cost: (current damcap bonus * 2) + 1 points.
    Example: 1st upgrade costs 1 point, 2nd costs 3 points, 3rd costs 5.

  @@wreincarnate buy statcap@@W
    Raises the threshold before diminishing returns apply to your
    accumulated HP/Mana/Move reincarnation bonuses.
    Cost: (current statcap bonus)^2 + 1 points.
    Example: 1st upgrade costs 1 point, 2nd costs 2 points, 3rd costs 5.

@@yViewing Your Reincarnation Status:@@W
  @@Wreincarnate information@@W — Shows all reincarnation counts by class
  (mortal, remort, adept) and your current banked HP/Mana/Move bonuses,
  statcap bonus, damcap bonus, and available reincarnation points.
